# Function-body code generation (the Kotlin CodeGen's statement/expression
# layer, spec §12.2): checked TAST → JVM bytecode through the shared
# AdtClassWriter. Kotlin threads mutable fields (mv, nextSlot, loopStack,
# pending lambda queues, const fields); here they live in the Gen record,
# threaded exactly like the checker's Cx. Every gen_* returns (Gen, Bool):
# the Bool is Kotlin's "falls through" (false = control already transferred).

